Introduction

Yoon Bomi is a South Korean singer, songwriter, and actress. She made her official debut on April 19, 2011 as the main dancer and lead vocalist of the girl group APINK under Choi Creative Lab. She is also a member of the Apink CHOBOM sub-unit with Chorong.

Bomi made her debut as a musical actress in 2022 with the musical "Wonder Ticket - Resurrection of the Guardian Tree".

Bomi is known for her cute and quirky personality which was showcased through her appearance in different variety shows. She used to do gorilla impressions which made her memorable among viewers.

She played the role of 'Secretary Na' in the drama "Queen of Tears" in 2024 for which she gained immense praise for her acting.
